headline: Why Teradyne Stock Slumped This Week (Hint: Tariffs Are Starting to Hurt)
summary: Second-quarter revenue growth is now expected to be flat to down 10% from the first quarter, compared to a prior expectation of 5% to 10% growth.  Full-year revenue growth is now expected to be up 5% to 10%, compared to a prior expectation of 15%.
